                            <comment id="17563361" author="houston" created="Wed, 6 Jul 2022 17:59:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;So currently this does not work. If you test the solr-site htaccess yourself locally, it should work (or at least it did for me).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;However, when trying out URLs on the staging, or official site, the Headers are not returned.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;URLs to test with:&lt;br/&gt;
Should have the header added: &lt;a href=&quot;https://solr.staged.apache.org/guide/8_5/streaming-expressions.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://solr.staged.apache.org/guide/8_5/streaming-expressions.html&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
Should not have the header added: &lt;a href=&quot;https://solr.staged.apache.org/guide/8_11/blob-store-api.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://solr.staged.apache.org/guide/8_11/blob-store-api.html&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;ASF Infra did not seem to have an answer, but we should follow up with a ticket for them.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17622424" author="risdenk" created="Fri, 21 Oct 2022 19:04:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=houston&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;houston&quot;&gt;houston&lt;/a&gt; did an INFRA ticket get created for this? I don&apos;t see it linked.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17622430" author="houston" created="Fri, 21 Oct 2022 19:16:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Unfortunately not, just a slack discussion that didn&apos;t really go anywhere...&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://the-asf.slack.com/archives/CBX4TSBQ8/p1656615770850289&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://the-asf.slack.com/archives/CBX4TSBQ8/p1656615770850289&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I should make one though, it is very very annoying that this doesn&apos;t work.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17943642" author="houston" created="Fri, 11 Apr 2025 17:17:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve given up on the robots header option in the htaccess file. Instead, and even better for customizability, we will add canonical links to our old Ref Guide pages. This is what Antora does for new ref guide pages, so it&apos;s perfect.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17944788" author="jira-bot" created="Tue, 15 Apr 2025 16:52:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Commit ad7ceb7ad71eb4279c3b530fb2ba53e5ee3e1ec2 in solr&apos;s branch refs/heads/main from Houston Putman&lt;br/&gt;
[ &lt;a href=&quot;https://gitbox.apache.org/repos/asf?p=solr.git;h=ad7ceb7ad71&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://gitbox.apache.org/repos/asf?p=solr.git;h=ad7ceb7ad71&lt;/a&gt; ]&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-16262&quot; title=&quot;Make sure Search Engines only know about most recent version of a ref-guide page&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-16262&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-16262&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: Add a script to add canonical links to Solr 6-8 ref guide pages (#3319)&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="17945746" author="houston" created="Fri, 18 Apr 2025 20:03:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m not sure this worked.... Maybe I should try adding a &lt;tt&gt;&amp;lt;meta name=&quot;robots&quot; content=&quot;noindex&quot;&amp;gt;&lt;/tt&gt; tag to the header, in addition to the canonical link.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17946464" author="jira-bot" created="Tue, 22 Apr 2025 16:12:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Commit ee97f7cefbec8db442f694f343a52e1f51070247 in solr&apos;s branch refs/heads/main from Houston Putman&lt;br/&gt;
[ &lt;a href=&quot;https://gitbox.apache.org/repos/asf?p=solr.git;h=ee97f7cefbe&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://gitbox.apache.org/repos/asf?p=solr.git;h=ee97f7cefbe&lt;/a&gt; ]&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-16262&quot; title=&quot;Make sure Search Engines only know about most recent version of a ref-guide page&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-16262&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-16262&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: Canonical URL script should add noindex robots meta tags&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="18033613" author="houston" created="Tue, 28 Oct 2025 17:07:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Ok, so after like half a year, Google has finally gone and reindexed all the old ref guide pages. This is now done. We are good to go!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
